==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Residuum
<hw>Re*sid"u*um</hw> <pr>(-?m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. See
<er>Residue</er>.]</ety> <def>That which is left after any process of
separation or purification; that which remains after certain specified
deductions are made; residue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>⟦ldquo⟧I think so,⟦rdquo⟧ is the whole <qex>residuum</qex> . . .
after evaporating the prodigious pretensions of the zealot
demagogue.</q> <rj><qau>L. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resiege</ent>⟦br⟧
